        <etym xml:lang="ru">Слово иранское (основа <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                                        ><lang/><w>zar-</w><gloss><q>обижать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="ira"><w/><gloss><q>огорчать</q></gloss></mentioned>, с префиксом
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>а-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>ā-zar</w></mentioned>, но в осетинском стоит
                настолько изолированно, что должно быть рассматриваемо как усвоенное из персидского:
                        <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                        ><lang/><w>āzār</w><gloss><q>обида</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>огорчение</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>болезнь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>мука</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
                        xml:lang="trk"><lang/><w>azar</w></mentioned> id., <mentioned xml:lang=""
                                ><lang/><w>ʽazar</w></mentioned>. На иранской почве ср. также
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*āzār(ʼʼz’r)</w></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="sog"
                        ><w>*āzārm(ʼʼzrm)</w><gloss><q>оскорбление</q></gloss></mentioned>, ,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
                                ><lang/><w>āzār-</w><gloss><q>оскорблять</q></gloss></mentioned>.
                Осетинский дает существенное смещение значения.<note n="1"> PUT NOTE HERE
                </note></etym>
        <etym xml:lang="en">The word is Iranian (stem<mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                                        ><lang/><w>zar-</w><gloss><q>offend</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="ira"><w/><gloss><q>grieve</q></gloss></mentioned>, with
                        prefix<mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>а-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>ā-zar</w></mentioned>, but in Ossetic it is so
                isolated that it should be considered as learned from Persian:<mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"
                        ><lang/><w>āzār</w><gloss><q>offense</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>grief</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>disease</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>torment</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
                        xml:lang="trk"><lang/><w>azar</w></mentioned> id., <mentioned xml:lang=""
                                ><lang/><w>ʽazar</w></mentioned>. On Iranian ground, cf. also
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*āzār(ʼʼz’r)</w></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="sog"><w>*āzārm(ʼʼzrm)</w><gloss><q>insult</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                , <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
                        ><lang/><w>āzār-</w><gloss><q>offend</q></gloss></mentioned>. The Ossetic
                exhibits a significant shift in meaning.<note n="1"> PUT NOTE HERE </note></etym>
